Company Overview:
Founded over 20 years ago and headquartered in Arlington, Virginia, The Intelligence & Security Academy, LLC provides consulting services to federal clients in Intelligence and National Security matters and specializes in delivering strategic consulting and innovative solutions. ISA also provides education & training to federal government agencies as well as private sector companies and academic institutions in the areas of intelligence analysis, budget formulation policy development, and more. Our company also delivers systems engineering and engineering management services to federal clients that focus on the design, development, integration, and management of complex systems.
 Job Description:
ISA is seeking data analysts to support our consulting and advisory services to Department of Defense (DoD) customers. Our projects require dynamic individuals who possess skills in data sciences, information technology (IT), strategic thinking, solutions development, business process improvement, policy research, and presentation design.
Work Model:
Our people-first culture prioritizes the benefits of flexibility and collaboration, whether that happens in person or remotely. Consistent with government and industry standards that support a more fulsome return to in-office culture, ISA supports our clients and provides a working environment that promotes professional development opportunities through peer engagement and face-to-face mentoring. The ability to meet across teams at the office and cross-pollinate information is critical to our success.

If this position is listed as onsite, you'll work with colleagues and clients in person, as needed for the specific role. (This is the ISA standard/preferred work model.)
If this position is a remote position, you'll primarily work as a remote employee, but may periodically work from an ISA or client site facility. (This work model is only used when a position cannot otherwise be filled with onsite personnel and is allowable by client requirements. This work model is offered as required only.

 Responsibilities:
The candidate shall have experience and demonstrated competency in analytical roles. The candidate must possess strong written and oral communication skills and able to easily interact with senior-level directors and/or agency heads. Our Data Analysts will formulate and apply mathematical modeling and other optimizing methods to develop and interpret information that assists management with decision making, policy formulation, or other managerial functions. ISA team members may collect and analyze data and develop decision support software, service, or products, as well as develop and supply optimal time, financial management, or logistics analysis for program evaluation, review, or implementation.
The following skills are required:

Ability to work in a team environment and take initiative in solutions and product development
Excellent written and oral communication skills
Comfortable presenting to large audiences of varying seniority and experience levels in the topic area
All-source analytical competencies and familiarity with data sciences and methodologies
Wide-ranging experience with data and analytics presentation and visualization development
Ability to produce data visualizations using Microsoft Excel, Tableau, Microsoft Power BI, or equivalent.
Real-world, program/project-applied data analytics experience.
Some familiarity with DoD IT capabilities and/or architectures

Skills strongly desired:

Ability to code in Python/JAVA/R or similar language
Experience with developing solutions in Regex, SQL, or other similar tools
Experience with developing solutions in ServiceNow, Apptio or other Technology Business Management applications
Experience with MS Project
Familiar with DoD Financial Management data manipulation and analysis (Planning, Programming, Budget, & Execution)

 Duties:

Performing all-source research and data analysis to identify business, mission or operational trends and relevant issues.
Lead data method (observational, experimental, simulation, or derived) capture planning and implementation based on project requirements.
Briefing corporate and client stakeholders on all aspects of assigned project data services.
Drafting program requirements based on research data.
Drafting and revising procedural documents
Documenting program changes
Evaluating program and operational effectiveness
Collaborating with Program Managers to develop and implement new programs.
Tracking and documenting performance metrics across the organization
Presenting recommendations to management and other stakeholders
Create engaging presentations for corporate and client stakeholders.
Lead internal whiteboard solutions sessions and related engagements with action officer-level customers and stakeholders.
Assist Program leadership with senior-leader briefings through provision of subject matter expertise.
Track program/project status and schedules

 Supervisory Responsibilities: 
As necessary commensurate to position and ability. This position may require provision of 'Task Lead'-level leadership on ISA projects. Individual Task Leads will be expected to supervise, coordinate, and consolidate the inputs and efforts of Junior Analysts and Subject Matter Experts.
 Clearance Required:
Applicants must have at least an active Secret clearance and be able to obtain a clearance at the TS/SCI level. Preference will be given to those who have an active TS/SCI clearance. Applicants must be able to submit documentation establishing U.S. Person status upon hiring. All ISA employees are required to uphold and maintain trustworthiness and suitability requirements of the U.S. federal government.
 Experience Required:
Preferred 3-10 years of experience in ANY of the following: defense contracting, federal civilian employment, military service (to include National Guard and Reserve), or commercial industry
Education:
Requires bachelor's degree in ANY of the following: Date Science, Statistics, Math, Physics, Data Management, Political Science, Business Administration, Communications, Government, or Military History.
Compensation:
At ISA, we celebrate your contributions, provide you with opportunities and choices, and support your total well-being. Our offerings include 401(k) matching, PTO, paid Federal holidays, Life Insurance, Medical, Dental and Vision insurance, FSA/HSA options, professional development opportunities, and work-life programs. Our annual review program acknowledges employees for exceptional performance and superior demonstration of our values. Full-time employees working at least 30 hours a week on a regular basis are eligible to participate in ISA's full benefit program. Part-time employees that do not meet the threshold are only eligible for select offerings, not inclusive of health benefits. We encourage you to learn more about our total benefits by visiting https://www.isallc.net/isahrdownloads.

The salary range for this position starts at $60,000 and increases commensurate with years of experience, education, certifications, etc. and is just one component of ISA's total compensation package for employees.
Certification:
Data analyst and Cyber certifications desirable but not required.

 A Day In The Life The Sr. Principal Business Analyst supports various phases of product development from initial conception through to deployment and continuous improvement. They will work closely with the Product Owner and the project team, facilitating and executing a seamless integration of business processes with advanced data-driven insights. Key to this role is the ability to understand and document both current and future business needs, collaborating with internal stakeholders and external service providers to identify and implement the most effective IT solutions. The analyst must possess a strong analytical capability to manage and interpret data from diverse sources, ensuring data integrity and usefulness for making strategic decisions. The Sr. Principal Business Analyst helps ensure that data and analytics solutions meet user requirements and are in line with the strategic goals of the organization. Their work not only involves rigorous analysis and documentation but also ongoing collaboration and communication across various levels of the organization to champion the adoption of data-centric business solutions.
 


 As a Sr. Principal Business Analyst you will:
 

Supports the Product Owner and project team through various product phases like Process Analysis, Requirements, User Acceptance Testing, Training, Deployment, and Continuous Improvement.
Documents current and emerging business needs and works with internal and external service providers to define and deliver data and analytics solutions.
Participates in sessions to gather business context from Product Owners, analyze, document findings.
Documents business requirements, use stories, and technical requirements.
Collaborates with internal customers to ensure user requirements are complete and concise, confirming that changes and enhancements meet technical specifications and user requirements.
Performs data analysis on different data sources, consolidating multiple data sets and analyzing the data accurately and efficiently.
Performs business process analysis to define how data and analytic solutions should be configured to meet those needs.
Performs data analysis to review and analyze business performance prior to and post the deployment of data and analytic solutions. Using SQL, BI Reports and ad-hoc analysis within PowerBI, Tableau, Excel, and other applications.
Maps current processes to the desired state and identifies gaps such as program functions, output requirements, input requirements and sources, data conversion strategies, and system techniques and controls.
Assists with the development of test designs and develops test cases.
Assists with the development and maintenance of product and project documentation including internal project status and conceptual business communications materials.
This position may have direct reports depending on the project and organizational structure.



 What We Need From You


Bachelor's Degree Computer Science, Data Science, Mathematics, Engineering, or a related field. Req
8+ years of experience as a highly technical Business Analyst, Product Manager, Solutions Architect, Business Systems Analyst supporting data and analytic software development projects. Required
Experience working with Agile development methodology. Strong understanding of Agile methodologies and experience working in an Agile and hybrid development environment.
Strong prior participation in the design, development, and implementation of enterprise data and analytic solutions. A working understanding of applying data and analytics to improve business processes.
Ability to elicit, articulate and document process modeling, business requirements, description of business context using scenarios and user stories.
Strong foundational knowledge of Agile Methodology in application, as well as Product Development and the Software Development Life Cycle.
Proven experience with business and technical requirements analysis, elicitation, modeling, verification, and methodology development
Experience using JIRA and Confluence to support workflow.
Experience in various data and reporting tools such as SQL, PowerBI, Tableau, and Excel
Strong demonstrated experience with Microsoft applications such as PowerPoint and can pull together clear, concise, and convincing presentations using mockups, data, and written context.

The associate is regularly required to move about the office and around the corporate campus. The associate must frequently move up to 10 pounds and occasionally move up to 25 pounds.
